@page "/"

<PageTitle>MarkdownToRazor Server Demo</PageTitle>

<div class="hero-section">
    <h1>🚀 MarkdownToRazor Server Demo</h1>
    <p class="lead">Experience build-time code generation that converts markdown files into Blazor Razor pages!</p>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <h4>🎯 About This Demo</h4>
    <p class="mb-3">
        This Blazor Server application demonstrates <strong>build-time code generation</strong> using MarkdownToRazor. 
        Unlike the WASM demo (which shows runtime file discovery), this demo converts markdown files into 
        physical <code>.razor</code> pages during the build process.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-0">
        Check the <strong>Generated Pages</strong> section in the navigation menu to see pages that were 
        automatically created from markdown files in the <code>MDFilesToConvert/</code> directory.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>🏗️ How Build-Time Generation Works</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Author Content:</strong> Write markdown files with YAML frontmatter in <code>MDFilesToConvert/</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Build Process:</strong> Run <code>dotnet build</code> to trigger MSBuild code generation</li>
                    <li><strong>Generated Pages:</strong> Physical <code>.razor</code> files are created in <code>Pages/Generated/</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Automatic Routing:</strong> Pages are automatically routed based on frontmatter configuration</li>
                    <li><strong>Blazor Integration:</strong> Generated pages work like normal Blazor components</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>✨ Key Benefits</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                    <li>⚡ <strong>Performance:</strong> No runtime markdown processing</li>
                    <li>🔍 <strong>SEO-Friendly:</strong> Pre-generated static HTML content</li>
                    <li>🛠️ <strong>Type Safety:</strong> Full IntelliSense and compile-time checking</li>
                    <li>🔄 <strong>Hot Reload:</strong> Changes reflect immediately in development</li>
                    <li>📝 <strong>Easy Authoring:</strong> Write content in familiar markdown</li>
                    <li>🎨 <strong>Customizable:</strong> YAML frontmatter controls page behavior</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr class="my-5" />

<div class="alert alert-success">
    <h4>🔧 Try It Yourself!</h4>
    <p>To see build-time generation in action:</p>
    <ol class="mb-0">
        <li>Modify any <code>.md</code> file in the <code>MDFilesToConvert/</code> directory</li>
        <li>Run <code>dotnet build</code> to regenerate the pages</li>
        <li>Refresh this application to see your changes</li>
        <li>Check <code>Pages/Generated/</code> to see the physical <code>.razor</code> files that were created</li>
    </ol>
</div>

